05:26.034 --> 05:26.931
- Deidra.

05:27.827 --> 05:29.931
Deidra, what are you doing?

05:33.034 --> 05:35.827
[melancholy music]

05:43.793 --> 05:44.931
- "You and I" will
be released tomorrow

05:44.931 --> 05:47.896
and every urban black radio
station in the country

05:47.896 --> 05:52.344
will be picking
it up. [chuckles]

05:52.344 --> 05:54.000
Tammy, did you hear
what I just said?

05:56.344 --> 05:57.931
- She should have been here
30 minutes ago, Charles.

06:03.034 --> 06:05.000
- This is just her way
of defining the terms.

06:06.793 --> 06:07.931
All right, it's what she does.

06:08.724 --> 06:11.896
- How could you be so
calm about all of this?

06:13.827 --> 06:14.896
- Well, because you're
nervous enough for both of us.

06:20.034 --> 06:21.000
Look, now I'm open
to many things,

06:22.862 --> 06:24.000
but giving up my son
is not an option.

06:28.034 --> 06:30.724
- I know we agreed to
leave our past in the past,

06:33.034 --> 06:35.862
but what happened
between you and Deidra?

06:40.689 --> 06:43.586
[doorbell ringing]

06:46.172 --> 06:48.827
[tense music]

06:56.137 --> 06:57.482
- Deidra.

06:57.482 --> 06:57.965
- Charles.

07:04.241 --> 07:05.103
Where's Jay?

07:08.034 --> 07:10.172
- He has this little
basketball ritual

07:10.172 --> 07:11.482
he's obsessed with these days.

07:11.482 --> 07:13.103
I mean, I can go get him.

07:13.103 --> 07:15.103
- [Deidra] That's right,
the Steph Curry thing.

07:15.103 --> 07:16.034
He told me about it.

07:16.034 --> 07:17.482
No, it's fine.

07:17.482 --> 07:18.068
I think we need to talk.

07:19.793 --> 07:20.655
- Okay.

07:24.034 --> 07:25.931
- I was hoping that
we could speak alone,

07:25.931 --> 07:27.586
'cause what needs to be said

07:27.586 --> 07:30.862
shouldn't be said in front
of um, mixed company.

07:30.862 --> 07:32.620
- Whatever we need to talk about

07:32.620 --> 07:34.068
can be said in front of Tammy.

07:34.068 --> 07:35.655
- Charles, it's okay.

07:37.241 --> 07:38.103
You guys should talk.

07:56.103 --> 07:57.000
- So we're alone
just like you wanted.

07:58.896 --> 07:59.827
Let's talk.

08:01.931 --> 08:02.793
Uh.

08:08.724 --> 08:10.068
- You seem to have done
pretty well for yourself

08:10.068 --> 08:12.275
since our divorce.

08:12.275 --> 08:15.965
Can't help but wonder
if our little breakup

08:15.965 --> 08:18.000
inspired some of these hits.

08:19.620 --> 08:20.689
- Deidra.

08:20.689 --> 08:21.137
- Kidding.

08:23.241 --> 08:24.551
I am.

08:24.551 --> 08:26.000
You're a great producer.

08:27.137 --> 08:27.827
That's why I fell
in love with you.

08:30.551 --> 08:31.000
But you married a star.

08:33.137 --> 08:36.206
She's not me, but she's
a star nonetheless.

08:36.206 --> 08:38.000
- Look, I thought you
wanted to talk about Jay.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.172
- We are talking about Jay.

08:41.655 --> 08:42.827
I've been doing better,

08:43.862 --> 08:45.172
and so now I think it's time

08:45.172 --> 08:48.103
for me to be the mother
Jay needs me to be.

08:50.310 --> 08:53.000
- And that's why I'm allowing
you to spend time with Jay.

08:53.000 --> 08:54.137
Now after the hospital
discharged you,

08:54.137 --> 08:55.551
I knew it was important
for Jay to see his mother,

08:55.551 --> 08:57.000
but why full custody?

08:57.000 --> 08:58.137
I mean, his life is stable.

09:00.172 --> 09:03.172
- I'm his mother and I
know what's best for him.

09:03.172 --> 09:04.206
- Then why haven't
you been here?

09:05.793 --> 09:07.000
It's been me and Tammy, not you.

09:08.379 --> 09:10.068
- Tammy isn't his real mother.

09:11.241 --> 09:12.758
She's gotta go on tour.

09:12.758 --> 09:13.689
She's gotta record.

09:13.689 --> 09:16.310
He's my blood and not hers.

09:16.310 --> 09:17.758
This is our family.

09:17.758 --> 09:20.137
- And Tammy is a part
of that now, Deidra.

09:20.137 --> 09:21.206
- But can you do it without me?

09:23.000 --> 09:23.862
Look at this room.

09:24.758 --> 09:27.758
Look, the awards, the prestige.

09:27.758 --> 09:30.206
There's not an
ounce of me in it.

09:30.206 --> 09:32.172
- I am not gonna
apologize for my success.

09:33.310 --> 09:34.000
- You erased me.

09:40.344 --> 09:43.724
But you're not gonna erase
me from Jay's life, too.

09:43.724 --> 09:46.172
A boy needs his mother.

09:51.137 --> 09:52.965
- Let's start with
a few sleepovers.

09:54.241 --> 09:54.931
Can we do that?

09:58.379 --> 09:59.137
- It's a start.

10:01.344 --> 10:04.068
[melancholy music]

10:18.137 --> 10:20.965
[birds chirping]

10:33.000 --> 10:34.241
- Mama.

10:34.241 --> 10:35.206
- Hi baby.
- Hey.

10:36.896 --> 10:37.758
- You ready to go?

10:37.758 --> 10:38.758
- I have to get my bag.

10:38.758 --> 10:40.310
- Okay, um, where's your dad?

10:41.793 --> 10:43.724
- You know dad, some trip.

10:43.724 --> 10:44.931
He'll be home tomorrow.

10:44.931 --> 10:47.241
- So you're alone with Tammy?

10:47.241 --> 10:49.827
- Yeah, Tammy and Aunt Pam
are out back doing yoga.

10:49.827 --> 10:50.724
I can go get them.

10:50.724 --> 10:51.862
- Nope, don't.

10:51.862 --> 10:53.724
Just go get your bag.

10:53.724 --> 10:55.103
I have a lot of surprises

10:55.103 --> 10:56.068
planned for you this
weekend, mister.

10:57.620 --> 10:58.758
- Okay, um, you
wanna see my room?

10:58.758 --> 10:59.206
- I shouldn't.

11:00.758 --> 11:02.206
- It's cool, they won't mind.

11:02.206 --> 11:03.068
Come on.

11:04.413 --> 11:05.275
Come on.

11:10.379 --> 11:11.206
- I'm proud of you, sis.

11:12.689 --> 11:13.310
The whole family is.

11:13.310 --> 11:14.000
- Thank you.

11:15.793 --> 11:17.137
You know it doesn't
even feel really yet.

11:18.275 --> 11:19.413
- It will.

11:19.413 --> 11:21.241
And when it does,

11:21.241 --> 11:22.448
I'm here to negotiate
your new contract.

11:22.448 --> 11:23.379
- Thank you.

11:23.379 --> 11:25.241
I'm just happy you're here.

11:25.241 --> 11:28.241
Sometimes I feel like the
third wheel around this place.

11:28.241 --> 11:30.689
- I thought Mr. Right
treated you like gold.

11:30.689 --> 11:32.000
- No, it is not that.

11:36.931 --> 11:37.931
It's Deidra.

11:39.034 --> 11:41.137
She haunts this place,

11:42.758 --> 11:45.000
and if I even mention her,
Charles completely shuts down.

11:46.448 --> 11:49.000
[tense music]

12:06.517 --> 12:07.344
- What do you think?

12:08.965 --> 12:10.000
- I love it.

12:11.758 --> 12:13.379
- Um, you know what?

12:13.379 --> 12:17.896
I think we should go to
someplace fancy for dinner.

12:17.896 --> 12:19.896
Why don't you grab a jacket,

12:19.896 --> 12:22.310
an extra outfit,
and something nice.

12:22.310 --> 12:23.172
You think you can do that?

12:24.379 --> 12:26.000
- Mom, this is me
you're talking to.

12:26.000 --> 12:27.310
- Okay then.

12:27.310 --> 12:30.827
Go and uh, get
something really nice.

12:30.827 --> 12:33.448
No basketball jerseys.

12:33.448 --> 12:34.310
- Okay.

12:35.310 --> 12:36.827
- Take your time.

12:36.827 --> 12:39.172
[tense music]

12:43.758 --> 12:44.862
- What do you know about her?

12:44.862 --> 12:47.448
- Uh, not much.

12:47.448 --> 12:49.206
Just that when Charles
filed for divorce,

12:50.482 --> 12:51.862
she took it really hard

12:51.862 --> 12:53.000
and disappeared when
Jay was younger.

12:55.758 --> 12:56.206
- [Pam] She disappeared?

12:57.827 --> 12:59.310
- [Tammy] I guess.

12:59.310 --> 13:02.241
But she is back now and
she appears to be stable

13:03.896 --> 13:06.448
and she's ready to be a mom
again, so I'm happy for her.

13:06.448 --> 13:08.517
Truly, I am, because
when she's good,

13:10.206 --> 13:10.413
that means that Jay's good.

13:14.344 --> 13:17.034
- But aren't you curious
about what happened?

13:17.034 --> 13:18.275
- Nah.

13:18.275 --> 13:20.931
I have to respect
that, you know?

13:20.931 --> 13:22.034
Let the past be the past.

13:23.172 --> 13:24.517
- [Pam] What about you?

13:24.517 --> 13:25.379
- [Tammy] What about me?

13:26.310 --> 13:27.034
- [Pam] As long as
Jay's under this roof,

13:27.034 --> 13:28.413
Deidre's gonna be coming around.

13:30.275 --> 13:31.241
You need to know what
you're up against.

13:32.827 --> 13:34.206
- What does that
mean, "Up against?"

13:35.448 --> 13:37.275
- If I was her,

13:37.275 --> 13:38.448
I'd wanna know everything
about the woman around my kid.

13:38.448 --> 13:41.241
Especially if she's
about to become

13:41.241 --> 13:42.931
the biggest star in the world.

13:42.931 --> 13:45.310
[tense music]

14:00.586 --> 14:01.448
- Mama.

14:06.000 --> 14:06.448
What are you doing
in dad's room?

14:08.000 --> 14:09.310
- I was looking
for the restroom.

14:10.413 --> 14:11.586
- Oh, okay.

14:11.586 --> 14:12.275
Come on, let's go.

14:14.655 --> 14:17.000
- You know,

14:17.000 --> 14:20.172
I just want Deidra to respect
me and the way I care for Jay,

14:20.172 --> 14:21.413
like I respect her.

14:21.413 --> 14:24.448
Besides, I wanna have
kids of my own one day.

14:24.448 --> 14:26.620
- Well, if she keeps
disrespecting my sister,

14:26.620 --> 14:29.517
I will show her how
real of a sister I am.

14:29.517 --> 14:30.965
- Ooh.

14:30.965 --> 14:32.448
- I'll stomp a hole
in her real quick.

14:32.448 --> 14:33.620
- What?

14:33.620 --> 14:35.448
- I'll knock her teeth out.
Don't get me started. Uhn-uh

14:37.413 --> 14:38.275
- T.

14:42.448 --> 14:46.586
- Uh, okay, so look,
I told Jay that I,

14:48.000 --> 14:48.620
I could have stayed in the car.

14:48.620 --> 14:49.413
If I overstepped.

14:49.413 --> 14:50.344
- Oh no, please, Deidre.

14:50.344 --> 14:51.448
Don't be silly, we're-

14:52.620 --> 14:54.000
- Thank you for allowing me

14:54.000 --> 14:55.275
to take my child
for the weekend.

14:57.413 --> 14:58.310
Um, you know what?

14:59.448 --> 15:02.034
I wanna apologize
about the other day.

15:02.034 --> 15:04.965
I'm truly grateful

15:04.965 --> 15:06.517
for everything that
you've done for my child.

15:08.724 --> 15:10.655
Is there any way that we
could just, I don't know.

15:12.482 --> 15:13.448
Can we start over?

15:16.310 --> 15:17.172
- I'd like that.

15:18.172 --> 15:19.655
- Cool, how about tonight?

15:21.344 --> 15:22.551
- Tonight?

15:22.551 --> 15:23.482
Um...

15:25.724 --> 15:26.482
- Yeah, my liquor cabinet,
it stays open pretty late.

15:28.413 --> 15:29.655
- Tonight may not
work, only because-

15:31.379 --> 15:32.551
- Oh, I get it, that's right.

15:32.551 --> 15:34.482
You probably have a bunch
of text messages to read.

15:34.482 --> 15:35.586
It's okay, it's cool.

15:37.034 --> 15:38.103
Come on baby, let's go.

15:38.103 --> 15:40.689
- Wait.
[ominous music]

15:40.689 --> 15:42.655
How late does your
liquor cabinet stay open?

15:44.482 --> 15:46.655
[tense music]

16:12.206 --> 16:13.275
- It's not much,

16:15.103 --> 16:16.517
but um, Jay has his own room

16:18.068 --> 16:19.344
and it's in a good
school district.

16:21.758 --> 16:23.241
- Um, I think it's great.

16:27.068 --> 16:28.275
- Let's do this.

16:30.379 --> 16:33.068
- Let's.

16:33.068 --> 16:34.758
- So how did you meet Charles?

16:34.758 --> 16:35.724
- Uh, my sister, Pam.

16:35.724 --> 16:36.655
- Pam.

16:37.724 --> 16:39.793
Cute.

16:39.793 --> 16:42.275
- Yeah, it's actually
a really funny story.

16:42.275 --> 16:42.620
So they were-
- A toast.

16:45.241 --> 16:45.724
- Okay.

16:47.379 --> 16:49.068
What are we toasting to?

16:49.068 --> 16:50.448
- You, silly.

16:51.413 --> 16:53.724
Your song, it's amazing.

16:55.655 --> 16:57.275
It's the prettiest song
that I've ever heard.

16:58.379 --> 16:59.241
- Thank you, Deidra.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.344
- I almost feel like I
have a connection to it.

17:03.482 --> 17:05.482
- Hmm.

17:05.482 --> 17:06.827
No, it's funny you say that

17:06.827 --> 17:09.620
because I felt the same
exact way when I heard it.

17:09.620 --> 17:11.137
- You heard it?

17:11.137 --> 17:12.620
- Yeah, the demo.

17:12.620 --> 17:15.172
Charles had written
it years ago,

17:15.172 --> 17:16.517
and when I heard this song,

17:18.344 --> 17:19.655
I just knew I had to sing it.

17:21.344 --> 17:23.206
- So he never released it?

17:23.206 --> 17:26.068
- Uh-uh, he said he could never
find the right voice for it,

17:26.068 --> 17:26.551
till now.

17:30.137 --> 17:32.344
- What exactly did
Charles tell you about me?

17:34.241 --> 17:36.344
- What does anybody ever
tell anyone about their ex?

17:36.344 --> 17:38.172
- Fair enough.
- Mm.

17:38.172 --> 17:40.172
[both chuckling]

17:40.172 --> 17:44.655
- Well, we met when I was
in my second year in college

17:44.655 --> 17:47.448
and he had just had
this serious breakup

17:47.448 --> 17:50.517
with Jessica Dawson.

17:52.482 --> 17:53.482
- Jessica Dawson.

17:55.655 --> 17:58.241
- By that look, you've
heard that name before.

17:59.655 --> 18:00.896
She really broke his heart.

18:00.896 --> 18:02.586
But her loss was my gain, right?

18:04.241 --> 18:07.310
And I was in school
for computer graphics,

18:07.310 --> 18:08.586
but he saw right through.

18:09.275 --> 18:10.689
He knew I wanted to make music.

18:10.689 --> 18:12.206
- So you sing.

18:12.206 --> 18:12.758
- Dabbled.

18:15.137 --> 18:18.551
You know Charles, he makes
you feel like a star.

18:18.551 --> 18:20.620
- Mm.

18:20.620 --> 18:24.241
- He used to keep his uh,
his songs in these journals.

18:24.241 --> 18:25.413
- Yeah, he still does that.

18:26.517 --> 18:28.724
- And we would go to the studio

18:28.724 --> 18:33.241
and we would record
these amazing love songs.

18:33.241 --> 18:36.758
But then it led to more love
making than making music.

18:38.862 --> 18:40.620
I think sex inspires him.

18:46.206 --> 18:47.793
