send him a naughty pic.

21:55.586 --> 21:56.724
- Ooh, do you like him?

21:56.724 --> 21:58.620
- Yeah, maybe, I don't know.

22:00.413 --> 22:01.344
- Hey, do it, okay?

22:01.344 --> 22:02.517
You only live once.

22:02.517 --> 22:04.413
What, is he cute?

22:04.413 --> 22:05.931
- You'll see him soon enough.

22:07.068 --> 22:07.965
- Okay.

22:09.724 --> 22:11.827
Well um, I should get going,

22:11.827 --> 22:13.931
but I'm really glad we
got the chance to do this.

22:13.931 --> 22:14.758
- Likewise.

22:16.068 --> 22:19.965
- Thank you, Deidra.

22:19.965 --> 22:22.000
- You, uh, tell Charles
to stay outta trouble.

22:24.034 --> 22:26.758
[melancholy music]

22:35.758 --> 22:37.965
[lively music]

22:58.758 --> 22:59.034
- Tammy.

23:00.965 --> 23:02.517
Tammy, why aren't you ready?

23:02.517 --> 23:04.413
We have a meeting with
Satellite Radio at 11 o'clock.

23:04.413 --> 23:05.482
All right, this industry
doesn't give second chances.

23:05.482 --> 23:07.551
We can't blow this.

23:07.551 --> 23:09.896
- You know, that's funny,
because you got a second chance.

23:12.137 --> 23:13.000
- What?

23:15.482 --> 23:17.896
- I went and saw
Deidre last night.

23:17.896 --> 23:18.758
- Why would you do that?

23:19.551 --> 23:21.068
- You know, probably
for the same reason

23:21.068 --> 23:22.034
you never told me why
you were arrested.

23:24.000 --> 23:25.103
- Look, baby.

23:25.103 --> 23:26.965
- Look, do not "baby" me.

23:28.862 --> 23:29.724
What the hell?

23:30.965 --> 23:32.482
- Look, it's the
past, all right?

23:32.482 --> 23:33.517
She's the past.

23:33.517 --> 23:35.034
All right, let it go.

23:35.034 --> 23:36.965
- Why didn't you tell
me that she sings,

23:36.965 --> 23:38.896
or anything about
her for that matter?

23:39.896 --> 23:40.758
Or should I let that go, too?

23:42.551 --> 23:42.896
What else are you
hiding from me, Charles?

23:44.620 --> 23:44.896
- It's not what you think.

23:47.724 --> 23:48.793
Look, I did it for Jay.

23:48.793 --> 23:53.034
Okay, I kept secrets for him.

23:58.137 --> 23:59.000
All right, look.

24:01.655 --> 24:03.551
I was arrested for assault.

24:03.551 --> 24:05.586
All right, some
guy said I hit him

24:05.586 --> 24:06.724
after I saw him and
Deidra flirting.

24:09.034 --> 24:10.241
I got jealous and
confronted him.

24:10.241 --> 24:12.103
- And did you hit him?

24:12.103 --> 24:13.896
- No, no, but the police
didn't believe me.

24:14.862 --> 24:16.551
I was a hothead back then

24:16.551 --> 24:18.827
and it wasn't the first time
I was in trouble with the law.

24:20.034 --> 24:20.965
- Not your first time?

24:22.862 --> 24:25.172
- Look, our
relationship was toxic.

24:25.172 --> 24:26.103
She reveled in the drama.

24:27.931 --> 24:31.000
- Yeah, but why
didn't you tell me?

24:31.000 --> 24:33.586
- Well, I had my
record expunged.

24:33.586 --> 24:35.034
Right, I paid a PR
team to erase me

24:35.034 --> 24:37.482
and Deidra's internet history

24:37.758 --> 24:38.965
because I didn't
want Jay to know

24:38.965 --> 24:41.000
he had a father
that was a criminal

24:41.000 --> 24:43.000
and a mother who went to a
mental health institution.

24:45.896 --> 24:48.206
Oh.

24:48.206 --> 24:49.965
I bet she left
that part out, too.

24:53.103 --> 24:54.793
- Well, did she sing?

24:56.724 --> 24:58.000
- Did she sing?

24:59.068 --> 24:59.965
Yeah, a little.

25:01.275 --> 25:03.965
But she wasn't a star.

25:03.965 --> 25:05.172
Not like you.

25:05.172 --> 25:06.724
- Charles, I am your wife.

25:06.724 --> 25:09.034
Do you know how stupid I felt?

25:09.034 --> 25:10.000
It's like I don't even know you.

25:12.275 --> 25:13.620
- Now you know me.

25:13.620 --> 25:15.862
- So does Deidra and Jessica.

25:18.034 --> 25:20.551
- Look, I know I betrayed
your trust in the past,

25:20.551 --> 25:24.137
and I know I don't deserve
it, but I'm asking you,

25:24.137 --> 25:25.034
look Tammy, you're
raising my son.

25:26.689 --> 25:28.862
Hell, I won't pretend that
I can do this without you.

25:32.655 --> 25:33.793
No more secrets, Tammy.

25:35.655 --> 25:36.103
Okay, I promise.

25:48.103 --> 25:49.965
- Deidra's not seeking
full custody anymore.

25:51.655 --> 25:52.000
She's okay with co-parenting.

25:54.793 --> 25:56.172
- Well, well how?

25:56.172 --> 25:57.793
I mean.

25:57.793 --> 25:59.137
- Does it matter?

25:59.137 --> 25:59.896
It's done.

26:03.241 --> 26:04.620
Hey, I mean, I don't
know what to say.

26:04.620 --> 26:06.034
I mean, I'm just-

26:06.034 --> 26:06.896
- You know what, Charles, just,

26:08.724 --> 26:10.965
promise me you'll be honest
with me from here on out.

26:12.379 --> 26:14.620
- Baby, I promise.

26:14.620 --> 26:17.000
[tense music]

26:30.206 --> 26:32.344
[tense music]

26:59.620 --> 27:02.275
[bowl clanging]

27:02.275 --> 27:04.413
[tense music]

27:53.413 --> 27:56.137
[Deidra sniffling]

27:58.206 --> 28:00.931
[lively music]

28:25.344 --> 28:26.758
- What is it?

28:26.758 --> 28:28.758
- Charles' file is sealed,

28:28.758 --> 28:30.000
but the other guy's file isn't.

28:31.172 --> 28:33.379
Jimmy Franklin, a real shit bag.

28:33.379 --> 28:36.344
Habitual criminal with
more assault charges

28:36.344 --> 28:37.241
than he has birthdays.

28:39.413 --> 28:41.517
- How will this help
me get to the truth?

28:41.517 --> 28:43.000
- Charles didn't do it.

28:44.310 --> 28:45.379
- He didn't?

28:45.379 --> 28:46.931
- Page six, superstar.

28:53.068 --> 28:55.379
- What is this I'm looking at?

28:55.379 --> 28:56.310
- It's a transcript
from a criminal case

28:56.310 --> 28:57.931
where Jimmy was a
state star witness.

29:00.137 --> 29:02.275
The defense attorney
raised concerns

29:02.275 --> 29:03.310
about his credibility
as a witness.

29:03.862 --> 29:05.275
He cites Charles's
case as his reason.

29:06.448 --> 29:08.551
- Hmm.

29:08.551 --> 29:12.379
Jimmy Franklin knowingly and
willingly pressed false charges

29:12.379 --> 29:15.137
on Charles Harper
only to drop his claim

29:15.689 --> 29:18.517
after his allegations
could not be corroborated.

29:20.034 --> 29:21.034
Why would he do that?

29:22.827 --> 29:24.137
- Why does any man do
what he does for a woman?

29:33.896 --> 29:35.586
- I gotta go.

29:35.586 --> 29:39.896
I have this IG Live thing I
have to do, but thank you.

29:39.896 --> 29:40.137
You're amazing.

29:41.344 --> 29:44.206
- Wait, be careful.

29:44.206 --> 29:46.034
That woman isn't playing
with a full deck.

29:48.068 --> 29:50.517
[tense music]

29:53.413 --> 29:55.206
- According to our records,

29:55.206 --> 29:56.965
you and Ms. Deidre Love
conspired against Mr. Harper.

29:59.068 --> 30:01.000
[assistant knocking on door]

30:01.000 --> 30:02.034
- [Assistant] We're ready
for you in five, Ms. Wilson.

30:02.034 --> 30:03.103
- I'll, I'll be right there.

30:04.448 --> 30:07.068
[tense music]

30:12.310 --> 30:14.448
Hey guys, so I'm gonna
answer some questions.

30:16.000 --> 30:18.103
What inspired "You and I?"

30:20.137 --> 30:23.517
I would say love,
pure, unfiltered love.

30:25.586 --> 30:29.137
And when I recorded it, it
was my hope that you guys,

30:29.137 --> 30:30.206
my fans, walk away
feeling that same love.

30:33.172 --> 30:34.137
- Unbelievable.

30:36.034 --> 30:37.103
- We need to talk.

30:39.034 --> 30:41.034
In my office, now.

30:41.034 --> 30:43.275
[tense music]

30:47.344 --> 30:50.344
[crickets chirping]

30:50.344 --> 30:52.206
- That doesn't matter.

30:52.206 --> 30:53.344
Look, we should be already
on the next single.

30:53.344 --> 30:54.448
Hell, the next three singles.

30:55.896 --> 30:58.241
Tammy is a star.

30:58.241 --> 31:00.413
The industry hasn't
seen an artist like her

31:00.413 --> 31:01.137
in over 10 years.

31:03.103 --> 31:05.379
Yeah, but we need something new,

31:05.379 --> 31:07.965
something fresh, something
vibrant, and have her-

31:07.965 --> 31:09.103
- We need to talk.

31:11.103 --> 31:12.965
- This is an important call
and I don't wanna fight.

31:14.379 --> 31:16.103
- So you think your
little Instagram post

31:16.103 --> 31:17.379
is gonna butter me up?

31:22.103 --> 31:25.000
- Um, I'm gonna have
to call you back.

31:25.000 --> 31:27.482
[sexy music]

32:36.310 --> 32:39.000
[calming music]

32:50.241 --> 32:51.586
- Cupcakes for lunch.

32:53.172 --> 32:53.655
Don't tell your dad.

32:57.310 --> 32:59.310
- Never, this is perfect.

32:59.310 --> 33:01.241
- I thought you might say that.

33:03.206 --> 33:04.517
So what's it like?

33:06.137 --> 33:08.000
Living with a superstar?

33:09.206 --> 33:10.103
- Who, Tammy?

33:11.758 --> 33:12.620
She's okay.

33:13.689 --> 33:14.413
- Okay?

33:14.413 --> 33:16.551
It's gotta be more than okay.

33:16.551 --> 33:18.758
Doesn't she go to
like award shows

33:18.758 --> 33:22.068
and parties with
celebrities and?

33:24.172 --> 33:24.620
- Nah, it's not like that.

33:26.586 --> 33:27.448
- Huh?

33:28.206 --> 33:29.620
What's it like?

33:32.103 --> 33:33.413
- She's mad Cool.

33:33.413 --> 33:35.275
Like super normal.

33:35.275 --> 33:37.586
She goes to my games
even when dad can't.

33:40.034 --> 33:41.655
- Growing up pretty
fast, mister.

33:41.655 --> 33:42.586
Even got your own key.

33:46.103 --> 33:48.068
- I'm not a kid anymore.

33:48.068 --> 33:50.068
Dad said it gives
me responsibility.

33:50.068 --> 33:50.586
- And he's very right.

33:51.758 --> 33:53.586
Let's see what else
you got on the court.

33:54.551 --> 33:56.724
Let me see your three
point, Mr. Big Time.

33:58.034 --> 34:02.827
- All right.

34:02.827 --> 34:03.655
- Was that all net?

34:11.724 --> 34:14.206
[phone beeping]

34:17.137 --> 34:17.827
Nice one.

34:30.379 --> 34:32.137
- What are you doing, mister?

34:32.137 --> 34:34.206
- Going through old
studio sessions.

34:34.206 --> 34:35.517
You know, the label's
thinking about doing

34:35.517 --> 34:37.517
a behind the scenes documentary.

34:37.517 --> 34:38.172
- Oh.

34:40.482 --> 34:41.724
Wait, oh my God.

34:43.103 --> 34:44.172
Stalker.

34:44.172 --> 34:46.241
[Charles laughs]

34:46.241 --> 34:47.344
How many videos do you have?

34:47.344 --> 34:48.689
- I record every session.

34:50.620 --> 34:51.827
- Do you ever stop working?

34:54.448 --> 34:56.413
- Doing music inspires me.

35:00.275 --> 35:01.551
You inspire me.

35:05.379 --> 35:05.896
- I don't deserve you.

35:11.275 --> 35:13.758
[doorbell ringing]

35:13.758 --> 35:15.482
I'll get that.

35:15.482 --> 35:16.896
- I'll get you some food.

35:16.896 --> 35:19.241
- Okay.
- All right.

35:19.241 --> 35:21.689
[tense music]

35:34.379 --> 35:36.793
- [Deidre Voiceover]
Jessica Dawson.

35:42.758 --> 35:43.931
- Oh baby.

35:43.931 --> 35:45.310
I thought we could
discuss the photo shoot

35:45.310 --> 35:46.724
tomorrow after lunch.

35:46.724 --> 35:50.793
- What is this?

35:50.793 --> 35:51.655
Open it.

35:53.241 --> 35:53.896
- What is it?

35:53.896 --> 35:54.896
- You tell me.

35:54.896 --> 35:55.758
Open it.

35:57.310 --> 35:58.206
- Jessica Dawson?

36:00.206 --> 36:01.620
This, this is a mistake.

36:02.689 --> 36:03.275
- Open it, Charles.

36:05.275 --> 36:05.931
- All right.

36:17.241 --> 36:19.862
All right, someone's playing
some kinda sick game.

36:19.862 --> 36:20.931
I don't know what this is.

36:20.931 --> 36:21.827
- Well then show me.

36:23.620 --> 36:25.931
Show me the joke.
- Baby.

36:25.931 --> 36:30.275
Baby, I don't know what this is.

36:30.275 --> 36:31.448
Don't you see how
crazy this looks?

36:31.448 --> 36:32.862
- No, your past is
what's crazy, Charles.

36:35.344 --> 36:36.689
- Read it.
- No.

36:36.689 --> 36:38.482
No, this is insane.

36:38.482 --> 36:39.862
Why would anyone
send me sex toys?

36:41.413 --> 36:42.275
- Let's find out.

36:48.827 --> 36:50.448
"My dearest Charles."

36:50.448 --> 36:52.448
"No matter how hard
we try to resist"

36:52.448 --> 36:55.586
"we keep finding our
way back to each other."

36:55.586 --> 36:58.275
"Last week was no different."

36:58.275 --> 36:59.448
"I can't stop
thinking about you."

36:59.448 --> 37:01.379
"Forever locked in."

37:01.379 --> 37:02.241
"Love, Jessica?"

37:04.448 --> 37:05.172
- Look, that's a lie.

37:05.172 --> 37:06.517
I haven't seen Jessica in years.

37:12.965 --> 37:13.862
Tammy.

37:19.896 --> 37:20.758
Tammy.

37:22.517 --> 37:24.413
Tammy, we need to
talk about this.

37:24.413 --> 37:25.275
Tammy.

37:26.931 --> 37:29.344
[lock clicking]

37:29.344 --> 37:32.551
[tense music]

37:32.551 --> 37:33.379
- Why are we leaving?

37:33.379 --> 37:34.379
I was just warming up.

37:34.379 --> 37:35.620
- I know, baby.

37:35.620 --> 37:37.344
I just, I have some
errands to run.

37:40.310 --> 37:41.000
Rain check?

37:47.275 --> 37:50.000
[ominous music]

37:50.000 --> 37:51.931
- Tammy, can you please
just open the door?

37:51.931 --> 37:53.379
Unlock the door.

37:53.379 --> 37:53.862
Let's talk about this.

37:55.413 --> 37:56.896
Look, you know me.

37:56.896 --> 37:58.551
None of this makes any sense.

37:58.551 --> 37:59.379
Just think about it.

38:01.068 --> 38:02.758
Okay, look, my phone.

38:02.758 --> 38:04.000
My, my phone is by the bed.

38:05.896 --> 38:06.827
You can check it yourself.

38:09.034 --> 38:10.034
Go on, check it.

38:18.448 --> 38:20.068
- What's the password, Charles?

38:20.068 --> 38:21.448
- It's Jay's birth year.

38:27.758 --> 38:28.482
Well say something.

38:30.000 --> 38:32.482
[phone beeping]

38:35.413 --> 38:36.689
- "Can't wait to see you."

38:36.689 --> 38:38.931
"Keep the cuffs,
I have the key?"

38:40.068 --> 38:40.965
- What?

38:42.517 --> 38:43.862
That doesn't even make sense.

39:17.034 --> 39:18.689
- Ready?

39:18.689 --> 39:19.862
- Why did we stop here?

39:21.862 --> 39:22.517
- Well,

39:25.172 --> 39:28.551
you're old enough to have
a key to your dad's house.

39:28.551 --> 39:32.413
I think you are responsible
enough to have a key to mine.

39:32.413 --> 39:33.482
I mean, ours.

39:36.103 --> 39:37.000
You have two houses now.

39:45.000 --> 39:46.137
- Where you going?

39:46.137 --> 39:48.034
- Out of my way.

39:48.034 --> 39:50.103
I can't stand to be in this
house around you anymore.

39:50.103 --> 39:51.482
- Because of an unknown number?

39:52.586 --> 39:53.620
Do I really look this stupid?

39:53.620 --> 39:54.482
- Do I?

39:56.965 --> 39:58.482
- Let's talk about this.

39:59.827 --> 40:01.724
- You know, why is
it the only time

40:01.724 --> 40:02.724
you're willing to
talk about your past

40:02.724 --> 40:04.931
is when it's blowing up
in your face, Charles?

40:06.896 --> 40:08.034
- Tammy,

40:08.034 --> 40:10.137
- Don't say my name.

40:10.137 --> 40:11.000
- Tammy.

40:12.137 --> 40:13.000
Can we?

40:15.103 --> 40:16.000
Baby.

40:17.758 --> 40:20.000
Let's think about
this, all right?

40:20.000 --> 40:22.034
Jessica doesn't
know where we live.

40:22.034 --> 40:24.034
Why would she do this?

40:24.034 --> 40:26.689
This has Deidre
written all over it.

40:26.689 --> 40:28.689
- Look, I don't care who did it.

40:28.689 --> 40:31.000
I'm getting sick and tired of
you and your ex's, Charles.

40:32.862 --> 40:34.482
I can't even look
at you right now.

40:34.482 --> 40:35.103
- Well-

40:35.103 --> 40:37.827
[tense music]

40:40.034 --> 40:40.862
- Dad.

40:42.620 --> 40:43.413
- Son.

40:47.482 --> 40:49.000
- You stay, I'll go.

40:53.758 --> 40:55.517
- He wanted to come home early.

41:18.206 --> 41:20.586
- [Tammy] It's just been a lot.

41:20.586 --> 41:22.103
- [Pam] Girl, it's
gonna be okay.

41:23.586 --> 41:24.551
But what's really going on?

41:27.068 --> 41:28.551
- Well, Charles is
staying at a hotel,

41:30.034 --> 41:31.172
and Jay is with Deidra.

41:33.724 --> 41:37.586
- Oh Tam, your
husband is famous.

41:37.586 --> 41:38.931
And with the hit new song,

41:40.241 --> 41:42.758
all his ex's will probably
come out of the woodwork.

41:42.758 --> 41:45.068
- Well, he needs to
get ahead of that.

41:45.068 --> 41:46.551
It is not my job
to manage his past.

41:46.551 --> 41:47.551
That's his job.

41:49.482 --> 41:51.206
- Now that sounds like a
bar for your next single.

41:54.241 --> 41:55.034
- Stop.

41:56.724 --> 41:59.034
- I can stay as
long as you want.

41:59.034 --> 42:00.793
- Oh, that's okay.

42:00.793 --> 42:02.103
I kind of wanna be alone.

42:02.103 --> 42:03.517
But thank you for
listening to me.

42:05.551 --> 42:06.068
- Of course.

42:14.758 --> 42:17.068
[tense music]

42:18.620 --> 42:20.620
[phone beeping]

42:20.620 --> 42:23.551
[tense music continues]

42:44.103 --> 42:45.586
[lock clicking]

42:45.586 --> 42:48.137
[tense music]

43:24.206 --> 43:25.724
- [Tammy Voiceover]
"My dearest Charles."

43:25.724 --> 43:27.896
"No matter how hard
we try to resist,"

43:27.896 --> 43:31.310
"we keep finding our
way back to each other."

43:31.310 --> 43:32.862
"Forever locked in."

43:32.862 --> 43:35.310
"Love, Jessica."

43:35.310 --> 43:37.724
[tense music]

44:05.413 --> 44:07.103
- Hi, this is Charles Harper.

44:07.103 --> 44:08.413
Please leave a message.

44:08.413 --> 44:10.310
- Hey, uh, Charles, can
you gimme a call back?

44:10.310 --> 44:12.241
It's, it's important.

44:13.241 --> 44:15.689
[tense music]

44:17.827 --> 44:19.379
Pam.

44:19.379 --> 44:21.758
- [Pam] Hey girl.

44:21.758 --> 44:22.758
Tam, is something wrong?

44:24.068 --> 44:26.689
- Um, I don't know yet.

44:28.034 --> 44:29.137
I can't get a hold of Charles.

44:30.758 --> 44:32.448
- [Pam] You're sounding off.

44:32.448 --> 44:34.758
- I saw something and it could
just be a weird coincidence,

44:34.758 --> 44:37.965
but something is not adding
up with that package.

44:37.965 --> 44:39.965
I need to do some digging.

44:39.965 --> 44:41.068
- [Pam] Do you need
me to come over?

44:41.068 --> 44:42.413
- No, I'll come to you.

44:42.413 --> 44:43.275
I'll see you soon.

44:44.862 --> 44:47.241
[tense music]

44:53.275 --> 44:56.172
- Hey, Tammy.
[ominous music]

44:58.275 --> 44:59.758
I know I'm early.

44:59.758 --> 45:00.482
I couldn't wait.

45:02.310 --> 45:05.034
You know, your pictures
don't do you justice.

45:05.034 --> 45:06.482
- Why are you in my house?

45:06.482 --> 45:08.827
- Whoa, ho ho, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

45:08.827 --> 45:09.310
Easy, girl.

45:10.310 --> 45:11.482
It's me, Zeeke.

45:13.034 --> 45:14.000
- I don't know who you are.

45:14.000 --> 45:15.379
Get out of my house!

45:15.379 --> 45:17.344
- Dating site.

45:17.344 --> 45:20.896
Brooding scorpio, lonely
housewife looking for some fun.

45:20.896 --> 45:23.137
Come on, you've been texting
me and begging me to come here.

45:23.137 --> 45:24.310
- Bullshit.

45:24.310 --> 45:26.862
- Tammy, don't chicken out now.

45:28.344 --> 45:30.172
- Come on, I drove a
long way just to be here.

45:33.310 --> 45:34.517
What are you doing?

45:34.517 --> 45:35.827
What are you doing
with this phone?

45:35.827 --> 45:37.034
What, what do you
doing with that?

45:37.034 --> 45:38.827
What do you think
you're doing, huh?

45:38.827 --> 45:40.482
Wanna start playing rough, huh?

45:40.482 --> 45:41.448
Is that what it is?

45:41.448 --> 45:43.034
You wanna start playing now?

45:43.034 --> 45:44.344
I guess we're getting
into it right away.

45:44.344 --> 45:46.482
[intense music]

45:47.793 --> 45:48.965
- No!

45:48.965 --> 45:49.827
- Shh.

45:52.275 --> 45:53.827
I know you said you
like it rough, but,

45:55.137 --> 45:56.965
I didn't imagine this good.

45:56.965 --> 45:58.241
Shh, you're feisty.

45:59.310 --> 46:01.551
But I like that.

46:01.551 --> 46:03.551
Are you gonna be a good girl?

46:03.551 --> 46:05.965
Are you going to be a good girl?

46:05.965 --> 46:08.000
Yeah?

46:08.000 --> 46:11.068
I mean, I'm just
following your lead.

46:11.068 --> 46:13.379
Now you're gonna
follow mine, right?

46:13.379 --> 46:14.862
Yeah?

46:14.862 --> 46:15.517
Good.

46:17.517 --> 46:20.034
This is fun, isn't it?

46:20.034 --> 46:22.344
Yeah.

46:22.344 --> 46:24.206
[Zeeke grunts]

46:24.206 --> 46:27.034
Hey, where do you think
you're going, huh?

46:27.034 --> 46:28.379
This was your idea.

46:28.379 --> 46:29.965
What are you talking about?

46:29.965 --> 46:30.931
So here I am.

46:30.931 --> 46:32.413
Let's play, huh?

46:32.413 --> 46:34.965
[Zeeke grunts]

46:34.965 --> 46:37.310
[tense music]

46:51.241 --> 46:54.241
[phone beeping]

46:54.241 --> 46:56.827
[Tammy crying]

46:59.206 --> 47:01.413
[tense music]

47:22.000 --> 47:23.482
[Tammy sniffling]

47:23.482 --> 47:26.862
[tense music continues]

47:45.448 --> 47:46.310
- What?

47:49.655 --> 47:50.344
What?

48:05.689 --> 48:08.379
[phone ringing]

48:15.344 --> 48:18.344
- Damn it, Zeeke, I said no
calls.

48:18.344 --> 48:20.965
[tense music]

48:32.379 --> 48:34.206
[dog barking]

48:34.206 --> 48:36.931
[ominous music]

48:39.068 --> 48:39.551
- Deidra?

48:43.000 --> 48:45.275
[tense music]

48:54.413 --> 48:58.034
[police radios chattering]

49:02.275 --> 49:03.275
- Miss Wilson?

49:05.344 --> 49:07.517
- I told you everything already.

49:09.448 --> 49:11.413
I told you about the call

49:11.413 --> 49:15.310
and I do not have a
My Gaze Only account.

49:15.310 --> 49:17.758
- I promise to look
into all of that.

49:17.758 --> 49:21.103
But I have a hard time with
one part of your story.

49:22.655 --> 49:23.517
- Okay?

49:24.655 --> 49:26.172
- He knew your address.

49:28.172 --> 49:29.172
Photos were taken of you.

49:30.551 --> 49:32.310
Text messages.

49:32.310 --> 49:33.551
- Yeah, they were all fake.

49:33.551 --> 49:36.275
I'm trying to tell
y'all, it's Deidra.

49:36.275 --> 49:39.172
I have never used an app
like that before in my life.

49:40.241 --> 49:41.448
- But this man had a key.

49:41.448 --> 49:42.517
Was that also fake?

49:43.586 --> 49:44.655
The alarm wasn't on.

49:44.655 --> 49:46.344
Is there a reason for that?

49:46.344 --> 49:48.448
- Because it's a safe
damn neighborhood.

49:50.655 --> 49:53.275
This, whatever this is, is over.

49:53.275 --> 49:54.724
- Excuse me?

49:54.724 --> 49:56.793
- Excuse me, I'm Pam
Newman, I'm her attorney.

49:56.793 --> 49:58.344
- I'm taking a statement.

49:58.344 --> 50:00.275
- Sounds to me like
you already have it.

50:00.275 --> 50:02.413
- I'm collecting facts.

50:02.413 --> 50:04.413
- Well, let me tell you
one fact you do know.

50:04.413 --> 50:05.551
A man broke into the home.

50:07.448 --> 50:09.793
- No, he entered
the home with a key.

50:09.793 --> 50:12.137
- And attacked my client
and she defended herself,

50:12.137 --> 50:14.655
which is her right.

50:14.655 --> 50:18.241
So if you're not sure what you
need from my client, leave.

50:19.482 --> 50:21.172
And call me when
you make a decision.

50:24.655 --> 50:25.517
- We'll be in touch.

50:37.241 --> 50:40.241
- You don't speak with
no one without me again.

50:40.241 --> 50:41.172
Do you hear me?

50:43.689 --> 50:45.517
I'm not going to let
anything happen to you.

50:46.655 --> 50:48.275
- It's gonna be okay.

50:49.379 --> 50:51.137
- Tammy?

50:51.137 --> 50:52.448
- Oh baby, are you okay?

50:52.448 --> 50:55.172
- I tried calling you.

50:55.172 --> 50:56.379
- Oh, I know.

50:56.379 --> 50:57.758
I'm sorry.

50:57.758 --> 50:58.620
How are you?

51:00.482 --> 51:02.724
- [Tammy] Detectives
think I invited him in.

51:02.724 --> 51:04.655
- Look, baby, I don't want you
to worry about any of that.

51:04.655 --> 51:06.413
We're going to take care of
it, I promise, all right?

51:08.413 --> 51:09.724
- You need to get
her out of here.

51:09.724 --> 51:11.586
- Yeah, I know.

51:12.172 --> 51:15.344
The media catches wind of
this it's gonna be a circus.

51:15.344 --> 51:17.068
Can we take your car?

51:17.068 --> 51:19.310
- Yes, but we're going to
need to make a statement.

51:19.310 --> 51:20.241
- I'm, I'm on it.

51:20.241 --> 51:21.517
- We need something now

51:21.517 --> 51:22.517
before someone else
creates the narrative.

51:22.517 --> 51:23.551
- [Charles] I'll figure it out.

51:23.551 --> 51:26.310
- [Pam] No, I'll handle it.

51:26.310 --> 51:29.482
You just get her as far
away from here as possible.

51:29.482 --> 51:30.689
I know a team that can
clean up the crime scene

51:30.689 --> 51:31.517
while we're away.

51:31.517 --> 51:33.068
- Just stop, stop.

51:36.689 --> 51:37.413
I'm not leaving.

51:39.724 --> 51:42.344
- We can't stay here.

51:42.344 --> 51:44.586
- So what, I'm supposed
to go out there?

51:44.586 --> 51:46.379
You think that's gonna
bring me peace of mind?

51:46.379 --> 51:47.689
- Tammy.

51:47.689 --> 51:50.655
- This is not a crime scene.

51:50.655 --> 51:53.344
This is our home and I
will not be run away.

51:54.206 --> 51:57.241
- Someone was in here.

51:58.551 --> 51:59.551
Now we need to think
smart about this

51:59.551 --> 52:01.413
until I can hire
a security team.

52:01.413 --> 52:02.724
I mean, what if there's
another deranged fan out there?

52:02.724 --> 52:04.310
- This wasn't a fan.

52:08.620 --> 52:09.655
It was Deidre.

52:11.517 --> 52:13.344
- Deidra?

52:13.344 --> 52:14.862
- Yes.

52:14.862 --> 52:16.689
Look, the pictures
were all fake.

52:18.793 --> 52:23.413
Yes, it was my face,
but it was not my body.

52:23.413 --> 52:24.655
- That doesn't mean it was her.

52:26.448 --> 52:27.689
Crazy fans make fake
photos all the time.

52:27.689 --> 52:28.862
- What about the call?

52:28.862 --> 52:30.896
- You didn't hear her voice.

52:30.896 --> 52:34.551
- Yeah, but my bangle
and, and, and lingerie.

52:34.551 --> 52:36.241
It was missing.
- Tammy.

52:37.620 --> 52:39.862
- So y'all think I'm crazy.

52:39.862 --> 52:43.862
- No, but we can't rock
the boat with Deidre

52:43.862 --> 52:46.896
or anyone right now.

52:46.896 --> 52:50.655
And making accusations we
can't prove can backfire on us.

52:50.655 --> 52:53.482
You're a person of
interest in a crime.

52:53.482 --> 52:54.655
A crime that could
sent you to jail

52:54.655 --> 52:56.793
for the rest of your
natural black life.

52:56.793 --> 52:58.896
If Deidre is behind this,

52:58.896 --> 53:01.965
tipping her off right now
that you suspect something

53:01.965 --> 53:04.275
isn't going to help.

53:04.275 --> 53:05.379
- So what, huh?

53:08.793 --> 53:11.620
What, you, you, you saying
I should do nothing?

53:11.620 --> 53:14.172
- I'm saying let me do my job.

53:17.655 --> 53:19.517
- Let, let us fix
this, all right?

53:19.517 --> 53:23.482
Let me worry about Jay and
we'll get through this together.

53:27.517 --> 53:29.517
All right?
- mm-hm.

53:29.517 --> 53:31.310
- It's gonna be okay.

53:36.827 --> 53:39.448
[lively music]

53:43.379 --> 53:45.448
- She's doing okay.

53:45.448 --> 53:47.793
Tonight was a difficult night.

53:47.793 --> 53:49.620
Tammy is resting comfortably

53:49.620 --> 53:50.689
surrounded by the
people who love her.

53:52.000 --> 53:53.620
Tammy's not only a celebrity,

53:53.620 --> 53:54.758
but she's a loving
wife and mother.

53:54.758 --> 53:56.379
- You lying bitch.
- We ask for privacy

53:56.379 --> 53:57.655
during this difficult time.

53:57.655 --> 53:59.655
- Ain't nobody's mother.
- Thank you.

53:59.655 --> 54:02.793
[reporters chattering]

54:04.827 --> 54:06.551
- It's a lie.

54:06.551 --> 54:07.758
Everyone on the internet

54:07.758 --> 54:09.034
is saying that Tammy
killed someone.

54:09.034 --> 54:10.793
- Oh no, it's true, baby.

54:13.517 --> 54:14.482
- I think I need
to be with them.

54:14.482 --> 54:16.034
- No, no, you're safe.

54:16.034 --> 54:17.586
You're safe here with me.

54:17.586 --> 54:19.724
- But Tammy needs me.

54:19.724 --> 54:20.931
She's always been there for me.

54:20.931 --> 54:22.724
- She needs you?

54:22.724 --> 54:24.862
She need a God damn lawyer.

54:24.862 --> 54:26.551
She not thinking
about you right now.

54:30.413 --> 54:31.862
- I'm going home.

54:31.862 --> 54:32.758
- You are home.

54:34.034 --> 54:36.758
- No, I'm calling dad.

54:36.758 --> 54:38.551
- He's busy.

54:38.551 --> 54:42.034
His wife just murdered somebody

54:42.034 --> 54:45.827
and she's facing jail time
for the rest of her life.

54:47.517 --> 54:48.448
She's not thinking about you.

54:48.448 --> 54:49.862
You should appreciate the fact

54:49.862 --> 54:51.724
that I'm trying to
keep you here safe.

54:53.034 --> 54:55.586
You acting just like
your damn daddy.

54:55.586 --> 54:57.827
- It's better than
acting like you.

54:57.827 --> 55:00.586
[hand smacking]

55:04.103 --> 55:04.827
- Jay?

55:09.551 --> 55:10.448
Shit.

55:16.586 --> 55:18.689
[Detective knocking on door]

55:29.103 --> 55:30.448
Can I help you?

55:30.931 --> 55:32.655
- I'm Detective Fletcher.

55:32.655 --> 55:33.965
- Oh, now is not a
good time, Officer.

55:33.965 --> 55:35.931
What, what's this about?

55:35.931 --> 55:38.482
- Just need to ask
a few questions.

55:38.482 --> 55:39.344
- About?

55:41.620 --> 55:43.620
- Are we able to go inside?

55:43.620 --> 55:45.413
- I'm on my way to work.

55:45.413 --> 55:46.931
- That's odd.

55:46.931 --> 55:48.655
You no longer work there.

55:48.655 --> 55:49.517
I checked.

55:56.758 --> 55:58.620
- How may I help you?

55:58.620 --> 56:00.000
- It's about your ex-husband.

56:00.000 --> 56:02.034
- Is this about last night?

56:02.034 --> 56:04.724
I was here with my son,

56:04.724 --> 56:06.413
and I'm afraid I
don't know anything.

56:10.103 --> 56:13.482
- How about I come
back at a later time?

56:15.965 --> 56:17.758
- That would be best.

56:34.896 --> 56:37.724
[Deidra screaming]

56:37.724 --> 56:40.586
[screen cracking]

56:40.586 --> 56:42.758
[tense music]

57:05.034 --> 57:06.862
- Mom?

57:06.862 --> 57:08.620
- Go to your room.

57:08.620 --> 57:09.758
- What is that?

57:09.758 --> 57:14.586
- Go to your room.

57:24.551 --> 57:26.724
Baby, I'm sorry.

57:28.103 --> 57:30.000
I would never do
anything to hurt you.

57:32.103 --> 57:35.103
What you saw is not
what you think you saw.

57:38.103 --> 57:40.896
And you're right about Tammy.

57:40.896 --> 57:42.034
She didn't kill anyone.

57:44.517 --> 57:47.896
What you saw in the room was
me trying to help the police.

57:50.034 --> 57:51.724
They asked me to help.

57:53.103 --> 57:54.793
I know this is scary,

57:56.103 --> 57:58.655
but I was just doing
my part trying to help.

58:02.068 --> 58:03.000
I'm sorry.

58:05.172 --> 58:07.172
They said somebody might
be trying to hurt me, too.

58:09.896 --> 58:11.620
- I will never let
anything happen to you.

58:13.103 --> 58:13.793
I'll protect you.

58:19.620 --> 58:20.862
- That's my baby.

58:27.310 --> 58:28.655
- Now what do we do?

58:30.862 --> 58:32.793
- We stick together.

58:32.793 --> 58:34.034
You and me.

58:40.758 --> 58:43.724
[people chattering]

58:45.896 --> 58:47.724
- They've been out
there all night.

58:47.724 --> 58:48.965
- [Pam] I'm working on that.

58:48.965 --> 58:50.862
I'll get the media to back off.

58:50.862 --> 58:53.034
- It's just, I know
Deidre's behind this.

58:53.034 --> 58:55.206
- [Pam] Anybody with
eyes can see that,

58:55.206 --> 58:59.034
but me having a law agree is
advising you to see what I see.

58:59.034 --> 59:01.241
- And what is that?

59:01.241 --> 59:03.034
- The police will subpoena
Deidre's internet provider

59:03.034 --> 59:05.137
for her IP address's activity.

59:05.137 --> 59:06.827
It'll be all over soon.

59:06.827 --> 59:07.689
She's done.

59:09.034 --> 59:09.965
- It doesn't feel that way.

59:11.931 --> 59:14.931
I need a favor,
from Detective Pam.

59:18.241 --> 59:20.724
- What do you mean Jay
doesn't want to come home?

59:22.310 --> 59:23.000
No, let me talk to him.

59:24.241 --> 59:25.793
I tried calling him all night.

59:25.793 --> 59:26.137
He's not answering his phone.

59:27.896 --> 59:29.000
Just put him on
the phone, Deidre.

59:31.000 --> 59:32.172
What?

59:32.172 --> 59:33.896
I don't need to calm down.

59:33.896 --> 59:35.241
What?

59:35.241 --> 59:37.000
You can't do that.

59:37.000 --> 59:37.862
Hello?

59:38.931 --> 59:40.206
Deidre.

59:40.206 --> 59:41.068
Damn it!

59:50.965 --> 59:51.965
How long you been
standing there?

59:53.137 --> 59:54.137
- Long enough.

59:57.068 --> 59:58.931
Go, you need to see him.

01:00:00.310 --> 01:00:01.931
- I'm, I'm not leaving you.

01:00:01.931 --> 01:00:04.896
- I am not a porcelain doll.

01:00:04.896 --> 01:00:06.103
Jay needs you, go check on him.

01:00:19.862 --> 01:00:21.137
[tense music]

01:00:21.137 --> 01:00:24.862
[Charles knocking on door]

01:00:31.689 --> 01:00:33.000
- Where's Jay?

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:34.034
- Excuse me?

01:00:34.034 --> 01:00:35.068
- Where is he?

01:00:35.068 --> 01:00:36.068
We're leaving.

01:00:36.068 --> 01:00:36.931
- Wait, he, wait.

01:00:36.931 --> 01:00:37.931
He wants to stay.

01:00:37.931 --> 01:00:39.000
- I don't have time for this.

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:43.620
Jay, Jay.
- Calm down, calm down.

01:00:45.206 --> 01:00:47.241
Look, I'm not letting you
in here until you calm down.

01:00:47.241 --> 01:00:49.965
We are going to speak as adults.

01:00:49.965 --> 01:00:53.172
That boy is scared
enough as it is already.

01:01:01.137 --> 01:01:02.931
- How did you get these so fast?

01:01:03.517 --> 01:01:05.000
- [Pam] I don't
disclose my techniques.

01:01:06.827 --> 01:01:09.862
- Wow they look so real.

01:01:09.862 --> 01:01:10.586
- It's a deep fake.

01:01:10.586 --> 01:01:11.206
She's crazier than I thought.

01:01:12.448 --> 01:01:14.310
- Yeah, but why?

01:01:14.310 --> 01:01:16.241
Charles was open to having
her be in Jay's life.

01:01:16.241 --> 01:01:17.862
I just...

01:01:17.862 --> 01:01:19.448
- [Pam] Something must
have triggered her.

01:01:19.448 --> 01:01:22.241
[tense music]

01:01:24.413 --> 01:01:28.034
- It's the prettiest song
that I've ever heard.

01:01:28.034 --> 01:01:29.689
I feel like I have a,
a connection to it.

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:33.862
- You know what?

01:01:35.310 --> 01:01:36.137
Let me call you back.

01:01:38.413 --> 01:01:40.137
- Are you really gonna
keep me from my son?

01:01:42.275 --> 01:01:43.310
What the hell are
you doing, Deidra?

01:01:44.827 --> 01:01:46.310
- What am I doing?

01:01:46.310 --> 01:01:49.965
Uh, someone was
killed in your house,

01:01:49.965 --> 01:01:51.827
and you really want
him to go back to that?

01:01:51.827 --> 01:01:53.310
- Then we'll leave.

01:01:53.310 --> 01:01:54.758
- Oh, okay.

01:01:54.758 --> 01:01:56.000
He'll love that.

01:01:57.310 --> 01:02:00.137
Another move in the
middle of the school year.

01:02:00.137 --> 01:02:03.137
- And let me guess, being with
you was the only solution?

01:02:03.137 --> 01:02:05.241
- Last time I checked, no
one died in my living room.

01:02:09.034 --> 01:02:11.137
Jay is a child.

01:02:11.137 --> 01:02:14.827
He needs time to process.

01:02:14.827 --> 01:02:16.896
He's safer here.

01:02:16.896 --> 01:02:18.034
- He's safe with me.

01:02:18.034 --> 01:02:20.172
- That's not good enough for me.

01:02:20.172 --> 01:02:22.379
- Not good enough, for you?

01:02:24.068 --> 01:02:26.206
- I'm doing what's
best for my son.

01:02:27.931 --> 01:02:29.310
- By brainwashing
him against me?

01:02:30.275 --> 01:02:32.206
- Last time I saw your wife,

01:02:32.206 --> 01:02:35.206
she was leaving with a suitcase,

01:02:35.206 --> 01:02:38.137
and the next day
she's killing someone.

01:02:38.137 --> 01:02:40.344
Your house is unstable,

01:02:40.344 --> 01:02:42.241
and it's been like
that for a minute.

01:02:44.482 --> 01:02:49.068
I'd be happy to talk to the
press about my concerns.

01:02:51.034 --> 01:02:53.310
- [Charles] Oh, so this
is what it comes down to?

01:02:53.310 --> 01:02:55.758
Okay, let's cut the bullshit.

01:02:57.896 --> 01:02:59.000
What do you want?

01:02:59.896 --> 01:03:03.448
- I want our son safe.

01:03:04.517 --> 01:03:06.310
I'm looking out for him.

01:03:06.310 --> 01:03:09.034
Someone has to and clearly
Tammy can't do that.

01:03:10.137 --> 01:03:12.000
- This isn't about Tammy.

01:03:13.034 --> 01:03:15.137
This is about you and me.

01:03:19.034 --> 01:03:22.206
- You made it about Tammy
when you gave her our song.

01:03:24.344 --> 01:03:25.241
- Song?

01:03:27.206 --> 01:03:28.827
What, what, what are
you talking about?

01:03:31.517 --> 01:03:32.310
You're crazy.

01:03:33.344 --> 01:03:34.827
- And your wife is a killer.

01:03:37.206 --> 01:03:39.310
You sure know how to
pick 'em, Charles.

01:03:40.448 --> 01:03:43.000
[tense music]

01:03:55.068 --> 01:03:59.275
♪ Love me right, love
me right, do me right ♪

01:04:01.620 --> 01:04:05.896
♪ Why do you, hold me tight,
never lie, you're right ♪

01:04:08.413 --> 01:04:11.206
♪ You and I

01:04:11.206 --> 01:04:15.034
♪ You and I, you and I

01:04:15.034 --> 01:04:18.034
♪ You and I, you and I

01:04:19.344 --> 01:04:23.206
- I'm not leaving
without my son.

01:04:33.103 --> 01:04:35.379
- Can I at least
collect his things

01:04:37.103 --> 01:04:40.310
and explain to him
why he has to go?

01:04:43.344 --> 01:04:44.137
- Okay.

01:04:48.965 --> 01:04:50.448
- Wait here.

01:04:50.448 --> 01:04:53.034
[tense music]

01:04:59.413 --> 01:05:01.586
- [Charles] Hey,
is everything okay?

01:05:01.586 --> 01:05:03.413
- Charles, Deidre sang
the demo for "You and I?"

01:05:04.586 --> 01:05:06.344
- No, I mean, yeah, yeah.

01:05:08.172 --> 01:05:10.206
Look, it's complicated.

01:05:10.206 --> 01:05:12.413
- Uncomplicate it for me.

01:05:12.413 --> 01:05:13.344
- [Charles] Tammy, it's
not what you think.

01:05:13.344 --> 01:05:15.448
- Enough with the cryptic talk.

01:05:18.689 --> 01:05:20.586
- Look, all right,

01:05:20.586 --> 01:05:22.103
we played around with the
song in the studio once,

01:05:22.103 --> 01:05:23.517
like 13 years ago.

01:05:23.517 --> 01:05:25.241
It wasn't for a demo, right?

01:05:25.241 --> 01:05:26.586
It was for us.

01:05:26.586 --> 01:05:28.206
We were just being
silly, it was nothing.

01:05:28.206 --> 01:05:31.172
- Yeah, but it was
everything to Deidre.

01:05:31.172 --> 01:05:34.586
You know, in her mind,
she thinks that I'm
singing her song.

01:05:34.586 --> 01:05:36.448
The song that you
wrote for her family.

01:05:38.344 --> 01:05:40.413
The family that
I'm a part of now.

01:05:40.413 --> 01:05:42.413
- Look, I didn't expect-

01:05:42.413 --> 01:05:44.172
- I told you to promise me

01:05:44.172 --> 01:05:46.103
that you would always be
honest with me about your past.

01:05:46.103 --> 01:05:48.586
And here I am finding out
another secret you hid from me.

01:05:49.689 --> 01:05:52.413
- [Charles] I'm sorry.

01:05:52.413 --> 01:05:54.965
- Your sorry's are starting to
become meaningless, Charles.

01:05:57.241 --> 01:05:59.103
Let me know when you
and Jay are on the way.

01:06:00.137 --> 01:06:01.000
- Tammy.

01:06:04.758 --> 01:06:05.413
Damn.

01:06:07.655 --> 01:06:10.344
[ominous music]

01:06:11.551 --> 01:06:14.137
[stick thumping]

01:06:14.137 --> 01:06:16.551
[body thudding]

01:06:21.137 --> 01:06:23.344
- Jay, let's go.

01:06:26.172 --> 01:06:27.448
- Is dad mad?

01:06:27.448 --> 01:06:28.413
- No, but we're
leaving, let's go.

01:06:29.482 --> 01:06:31.275
- Where to?

01:06:31.275 --> 01:06:33.137
- I don't have time to
answer any of your questions.

01:06:33.137 --> 01:06:34.172
Let's go.

01:06:36.172 --> 01:06:36.482
Just leave it.

01:06:38.137 --> 01:06:39.724
- But what about dad?

01:06:39.724 --> 01:06:43.172
- Boy, you'll be with
your dad soon, I promise.

01:06:43.172 --> 01:06:43.413
- [Pam] The police tracked
the IP address back to Deidra.

01:06:44.655 --> 01:06:46.241
An arrest warrant
has been issued.

01:06:46.241 --> 01:06:47.344
They're on their way now.

01:06:48.137 --> 01:06:49.482
- So it's over.

01:06:49.482 --> 01:06:51.344
When she's arrested,

01:06:51.344 --> 01:06:54.482
I'll issue a press release and
you can rebuild your family,

01:06:54.482 --> 01:06:55.344
and all of this will be over.

01:06:58.620 --> 01:07:00.862
- I'm gonna call Charles,
but I love you, sis.

01:07:00.862 --> 01:07:01.724
Thank you.

01:07:03.172 --> 01:07:04.517
- I love you, too.

01:07:06.275 --> 01:07:08.551
[phone ringing]

01:07:19.586 --> 01:07:24.413
[Charles grunting]
[phone ringing]

01:07:37.206 --> 01:07:38.724
- Tammy?

01:07:38.724 --> 01:07:39.586
- Charles?

01:07:40.241 --> 01:07:42.482
Baby, you don't sound too good.

01:07:42.482 --> 01:07:43.517
Charles, speak to me.

01:07:45.241 --> 01:07:45.551
Are you okay?

01:07:47.413 --> 01:07:50.448
- I don't know. [grunting]

01:07:50.448 --> 01:07:52.862
I think, I think Deidra hit me.

01:07:52.862 --> 01:07:54.413
- What?

01:07:54.413 --> 01:07:55.413
- [Charles] She's lost her mind.

01:07:55.413 --> 01:07:57.206
- Okay, are, are you okay?

01:07:57.206 --> 01:07:58.724
Where's Jay?

01:07:58.724 --> 01:07:59.586
- I don't know.

01:08:01.793 --> 01:08:02.655
Jay?

01:08:04.448 --> 01:08:05.310
Jay?!

01:08:06.448 --> 01:08:07.724
- Charles, what is going on?

01:08:08.931 --> 01:08:09.793
- She has Jay.

01:08:11.448 --> 01:08:12.655
Call the police, now.

01:08:17.379 --> 01:08:18.724
- How is your burger?

01:08:24.517 --> 01:08:25.620
- Why are we here?

01:08:30.310 --> 01:08:34.758
- There's a lot of people that
don't wanna see us together.

01:08:35.275 --> 01:08:38.310
And Miss Pam is a lawyer
and she's gonna help us.

01:08:39.758 --> 01:08:42.310
- Then why don't we just
go to Aunt Pam's house?

01:08:42.310 --> 01:08:43.379
I know where it is from here.

01:08:43.379 --> 01:08:44.482
- It's too dangerous.

01:08:46.620 --> 01:08:47.793
She's gonna meet us here.

01:08:49.931 --> 01:08:52.379
- It's been over an hour.

01:08:52.379 --> 01:08:54.310
How much longer do we
have to sit out here for?

01:08:59.586 --> 01:09:01.379
- You know I love you, right?

01:09:04.896 --> 01:09:08.482
And I would never let
anything or anyone hurt you.

01:09:10.482 --> 01:09:11.827
I refuse to let that happen.

01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:14.862
- Okay.

01:09:19.689 --> 01:09:21.517
- Mommy's gonna go
away for a while.

01:09:22.586 --> 01:09:23.862
- I'm coming with you.

01:09:23.862 --> 01:09:24.724
- No, not this time.

01:09:27.551 --> 01:09:28.862
- But you said it yourself.

01:09:28.862 --> 01:09:29.862
I need to protect you.

01:09:31.551 --> 01:09:32.862
- And you have done
a wonderful job.

01:09:36.862 --> 01:09:37.689
- Where are you going?

01:09:37.689 --> 01:09:38.827
- It's not important.

01:09:41.517 --> 01:09:42.724
But what is important

01:09:44.793 --> 01:09:47.379
is that we got a chance to
spend some time together.

01:09:53.344 --> 01:09:54.379
- Okay, mom.

01:10:03.965 --> 01:10:06.689
[Deidra exhales]

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:10.517
[tense music]

01:10:50.689 --> 01:10:53.379
[ominous music]

01:11:06.896 --> 01:11:09.413
[metal clanging]

01:11:09.413 --> 01:11:12.241
[wheel clicking]

01:11:19.034 --> 01:11:22.241
[melancholy music]

01:11:37.758 --> 01:11:38.724
- She's waking up.

01:11:38.724 --> 01:11:39.724
Could you go get a nurse?

01:11:39.724 --> 01:11:40.551
- Okay.

01:11:44.724 --> 01:11:45.758
- Where am I?

01:11:45.758 --> 01:11:46.931
- There's been an accident.

01:11:50.034 --> 01:11:51.620
- I got it.
- Relax.

01:11:55.034 --> 01:11:56.827
- I don't remember anything.

01:11:56.827 --> 01:11:57.931
- Deidre's behind this.

01:11:57.931 --> 01:11:59.034
I know she is.

01:11:59.034 --> 01:12:00.655
She's desperate.

01:12:00.655 --> 01:12:02.586
She took Jay and ran, she's,

01:12:03.862 --> 01:12:06.655
you know, I'm afraid to think
of what she's even capable of.

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:09.482
You don't remember anything?

01:12:10.620 --> 01:12:12.931
- I can't remember.

01:12:12.931 --> 01:12:15.482
I wish I could remember
anything to bury the bitch.

01:12:17.482 --> 01:12:18.344
- It's okay.

01:12:21.103 --> 01:12:22.000
How do you feel?

01:12:23.965 --> 01:12:24.965
- I'm okay.

01:12:28.448 --> 01:12:29.620
- Okay, careful.

01:12:35.827 --> 01:12:37.586
- [Charles] So there's
nothing more you can do?

01:12:37.586 --> 01:12:38.931
- Sir, we're doing all we can.

01:12:38.931 --> 01:12:40.655
- All you can?

01:12:40.655 --> 01:12:41.827
My wife told you

01:12:43.517 --> 01:12:45.034
that Deidra was behind
us from the beginning.

01:12:45.034 --> 01:12:47.689
If you had arrested her, none
of this would be happening.

01:12:47.689 --> 01:12:49.517
- That's not the way
it works, Mr. Harper.

01:12:49.517 --> 01:12:51.103
I understand your frustration.

01:12:51.103 --> 01:12:51.827
- Do you?

01:12:53.724 --> 01:12:56.000
Because I don't think you do.

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:58.310
My son is missing.

01:12:59.517 --> 01:13:00.827
Someone is in the hospital.

01:13:00.827 --> 01:13:03.551
I was almost killed and
my wife was attacked.

01:13:08.034 --> 01:13:09.586
You don't understand shit.

01:13:11.724 --> 01:13:14.413
[phone buzzing]

01:13:16.896 --> 01:13:18.724
- Should I answer it?

01:13:18.724 --> 01:13:20.000
- Yeah.
- Put it on speaker.

01:13:23.896 --> 01:13:24.758
- Hello?

01:13:26.103 --> 01:13:27.413
- [Deidra] Do we
have an audience?

01:13:29.724 --> 01:13:32.034
- Yes.

01:13:32.034 --> 01:13:35.758
- [Deidra] Take me
off speaker, just you.

01:13:35.758 --> 01:13:36.931
- Look, I need to
hear everything.

01:13:38.034 --> 01:13:40.586
- I will tell you everything.

01:13:40.586 --> 01:13:41.862
Just please let me handle this.

01:13:42.896 --> 01:13:44.413
- This could be our only chance.

01:13:46.034 --> 01:13:48.793
Just keep her on the phone
for as long as you can.

01:13:48.793 --> 01:13:50.034
- [Deidra] Are you there?

01:13:50.034 --> 01:13:51.758
- Um, yeah, I'm, I'm here.

01:13:53.034 --> 01:13:54.586
- [Deidra] Jay
wants to talk to you

01:13:54.586 --> 01:13:56.034
and I want this to be over.

01:13:56.034 --> 01:13:58.034
- Is he safe?

01:13:58.034 --> 01:13:59.034
- [Deidra] Let's just end this.

01:13:59.034 --> 01:14:00.965
Woman to woman, just you and me.

01:14:02.034 --> 01:14:04.000
If you do anything stupid,

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:06.034
you won't ever get
to see Jay again.

01:14:06.034 --> 01:14:08.724
Get rid of them
and call me back.

01:14:08.724 --> 01:14:10.827
- How am I supposed to do that?

01:14:10.827 --> 01:14:13.482
- [Deidra] You're a smart
girl, figure it out.

01:14:14.965 --> 01:14:16.655
- Okay, well, where are you?

01:14:16.655 --> 01:14:20.137
- Listen clearly, I don't care
what you say to them. You get

01:14:20.137 --> 01:14:25.620
- rid of them fast, and call me
when you're in your car alone

01:14:25.620 --> 01:14:26.482
Yeah.

01:14:34.724 --> 01:14:36.655
- So what'd she say?

01:14:36.655 --> 01:14:41.103
- She said that she's at
the old manufacturing plant.

01:14:41.896 --> 01:14:43.482
That you would
know where that is.

01:14:44.068 --> 01:14:45.758
- So she's there now with Jay?

01:14:45.758 --> 01:14:47.103
- Yeah, she's ready
to turn herself in.

01:14:47.103 --> 01:14:49.793
She, she has Jay.

01:14:49.793 --> 01:14:50.586
- Well, why didn't she call me?

01:14:50.586 --> 01:14:52.034
Why you?

01:14:52.034 --> 01:14:53.068
- I don't know, Charles.

01:14:54.758 --> 01:14:55.827
- The manufacturing plant.

01:14:55.827 --> 01:14:57.068
Do you know about this?

01:14:57.068 --> 01:14:58.827
- Yeah, yeah, I
know where it is.

01:14:58.827 --> 01:14:59.965
It's, it's an old plant where
I worked when we were married.

01:14:59.965 --> 01:15:01.275
- I need to move on this now.

01:15:01.275 --> 01:15:03.172
- No, no, no, look,
I need to be there.

01:15:03.172 --> 01:15:05.172
- No, I need you here
if something goes wrong.

01:15:05.172 --> 01:15:06.724
I will call you when
we have your son.

01:15:07.827 --> 01:15:08.793
- Thank you, Detective.

01:15:13.965 --> 01:15:14.965
Baby, are you okay?

01:15:16.034 --> 01:15:17.896
- No, I'm, I'm
worried about Jay.

01:15:19.310 --> 01:15:21.689
I can't stop thinking about Pam.

01:15:21.689 --> 01:15:23.137
This is hard.

01:15:23.137 --> 01:15:25.896
- I know, I know, babe.

01:15:25.896 --> 01:15:27.965
You know Pam, she's tough.

01:15:30.172 --> 01:15:34.172
Listen, why don't you
go be with your sister?

01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:38.034
All right, there's no
sense in her being alone.

01:15:38.034 --> 01:15:39.931
I'll call you when
I hear something.

01:15:39.931 --> 01:15:41.068
- Okay.
- All right?

01:15:59.724 --> 01:16:01.724
- Okay, I'm alone.

01:16:01.724 --> 01:16:03.172
- How'd you do it?

01:16:03.172 --> 01:16:04.379
- He's a man.

01:16:04.379 --> 01:16:06.068
He needed to be the
hero, so I let him.

01:16:08.068 --> 01:16:10.620
Now let's end this.

01:16:17.068 --> 01:16:19.620
[tense music]

01:16:29.241 --> 01:16:30.103
Deidra.

01:16:31.379 --> 01:16:36.241
[fire extinguisher clanking]
[ominous music]

01:16:38.758 --> 01:16:41.103
[smooth music]

01:16:50.344 --> 01:16:54.068
♪ Running out of
time, I can't wait ♪

01:16:54.068 --> 01:16:55.241
♪ 'Cause I'm afraid

01:16:55.241 --> 01:16:57.068
- Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

01:16:58.827 --> 01:16:59.862
Just listen.

01:17:01.034 --> 01:17:02.862
♪ I cannot replace

01:17:02.862 --> 01:17:05.275
Charles used to write
the most beautiful songs.

01:17:06.448 --> 01:17:11.103
When we met, he could barely
afford a session at this place.

01:17:15.034 --> 01:17:16.172
Now he owns it.

01:17:18.068 --> 01:17:19.275
Charles has everything.

01:17:19.896 --> 01:17:24.310
This studio, a beautiful wife,

01:17:26.448 --> 01:17:28.000
my son,

01:17:30.103 --> 01:17:32.275
and our song.

01:17:35.206 --> 01:17:36.793
What do I get, huh?

01:17:40.068 --> 01:17:41.931
[hand smacking]

01:17:41.931 --> 01:17:42.793
Answer me!

01:17:46.206 --> 01:17:47.275
- Where is Jay?

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:51.655
Oh, you think I
would hurt my son?

01:17:52.758 --> 01:17:53.862
He's fine.

01:17:55.310 --> 01:17:58.965
I told you, this
ends with you and me.

01:18:00.482 --> 01:18:03.275
♪ Never did this before,
I know I want more ♪

01:18:03.275 --> 01:18:05.344
We're toxic.

01:18:05.344 --> 01:18:08.275
I'm crazy, apparently,
but you're a murderer.

01:18:10.344 --> 01:18:13.275
Not the best role
models for my child,

01:18:13.275 --> 01:18:15.379
but Charles can start over.

01:18:15.379 --> 01:18:18.344
Maybe he'll do better next time.

01:18:21.517 --> 01:18:23.206
One hell of a song, huh?

01:18:26.000 --> 01:18:29.241
[ominous music]

01:18:29.241 --> 01:18:32.241
